history.text: Hi, how are you today?
Hello, I am doing fine. And you?
I'm great, thanks.  I got the movie Catch me if you can!   I love this movie.  Have you seen it yet?
No, I haven't. Who stars in it?
Leo DiCarprio and Tom Hanks.  It's based on a true event and back when it came out, my mom worked for a forms company and met the guy that its based off of.
That's pretty darn cool! Did the movie come out recently?
It's about a guy that is great at making fake documents.  He was a pilot, a doctor.  All kinds of stuff.
No, the movies came out in 2002, so it makes it 16 years old.
He must have been pretty good if he was able to fake being a doctor and a pilot! What was he doing when your mother got to meet him?
He was doing a seminar about how he is now helping the FBI to make it harder to do what he did.  (faking all the documents).  Thanks to him, we now have better watermarks and technology.
If you can't beat them, join them. I guess that's what the FBI did. Must be a cool story. Did you see it in the theater?

No, I am not big into going to the movies.  I usually wait till everything comes out on video. And yes, he definitely joined them.  I would love to meet him and have a sit-down conversation with him.  The movie portrayed him as a very likable guy.

Of course, I like all the actors in the movie.  Tom Hanks was his typical self.  He is great at the range of movies he can do.  From comedy to bio's.  Amy Adams was as popular back then as she is now.
I bet that would have been awesome. He probably has a lot more tricks up his sleeve.
So Leonardo played the main guy?
I'm sure he does.  You have to be good at something, if you can go from criminal to working with the FBI.
True that.
Yes, Leonardo was the main guy.  It showed his life from the beginning of his crime spree to the end where he got caught.  I believe he was only 17 when he started his adventure.
Oh, I couldn't even finish my math homework at 17, much less forge documents stating I was a doctor! Ha ha!
I agree.  He is a genius in my book.
Who is Amy Adams in the story?
The love interest?
Her character is Brenda Strong.  She married him in the movie.
Christopher Walken played his dad.

Yes, if the story is what I'm imagining, I agree with you. Society doesn't typically give enough credit to geniuses who work and think so 
outside the box.
Wow. Strong cast.
Looking over the info sheet, they have a 7.9/10 on Rotten Tomatoes.  I personally would have given it a 10/10.
Does it only give a Rotten Tomatoes score? Any IMDB Metascore?
It has a metacritic score, would that be what you are looking for?
That works too.
The metacritic score is 76/100.  with a cinemaScore of A-.
Overall, favorable scores. My opinion is anything with a Rotten Tomatoes score of over 7.0 is worth watching. So this movie would definitely be worth seeing based on that rating.
If you like Biographical movies about crime, this is one to see.
Doesn't have a lot of violence does it? I mean, it isn't filled with gore?
Doesn't sound like it, but have to ask.
If i recall correctly, there is a couple scenes where the shoot guns, but not any blood or gore.  Maybe a papercut at most as far as blood shed (or maybe a bloody nose from a good right hook)
Alright, sounds good! Any other cool information about it?
Not really, not without giving it away.  ;)
Yes! Thank you for not including spoilers (the good right hook doesn't count)
LOL.  Hope you have a wonderful day.  I hope my raving doesn't end with you not liking the movie.

uid2response.feedback: Pleasant discussion and movie came highly recommended. Will watch it.
